0039|- [HelpText]
0040|*The control codes for various graphical elements in PostScript plotting
0041|*are mostly the same as on other devices.
0042|*Line width is selected by [line_width(x)] where x is given in points
0043|*(1 point = 1/12 inches). Default value is x=0.48 .
0044|*Line types are selected by [line_type(x)] where possible values are
0045|*x=0,1,...,7. The line types are defined in PS.DEV as a vector /ltype.
0046|*The user can add more types and modify existing ones by editing PS.DEV.
0047|*Markings for points (in scatter diagrams, for example) defined by the
0048|*POINT specification are following:
0049|*0=black circle, 1=plus, 2=asterisk, 3=white circle, 4=cross, 5=white
0050|*square, 6=black square, 7=white triangle, 8=black triangle, 9=white
0051|Sdiamond, 10=black diamond, 21=arrow head, 22=filled arrow head.
